qas.question: What did Nasser do after the war ended?

answers.text: instructor at the Royal Military Academy

qas.question: What group did Nasser try to allign himself with?
What was the reason Nasser rejected the Muslim Brotherhood?
How did Nasser view the terms of the armisitce with Israel?
What region did the Israelis occupy during the talks?

context: After the war, Nasser returned to his role as an <a0_0>instructor at the Royal Military Academy<a0_0/>. He sent emissaries to forge an alliance with the <a1_0>Muslim Brotherhood<a1_0/> in October 1948, but soon concluded that the <a2_0>religious agenda<a2_0/> of the Brotherhood was not compatible with his nationalism. From then on, Nasser prevented the Brotherhood's influence over his cadres' activities without severing ties with the organization. Nasser was sent as a member of the Egyptian delegation to Rhodes in February 1949 to negotiate a formal armistice with Israel, and reportedly considered the terms to be <a3_0>humiliating<a3_0/>, particularly because the Israelis were able to easily occupy the <a4_0>Eilat<a4_0/> region while negotiating with the Arabs in March.
